The paper proposes an information-theoretic framework for matrix completion, which suggests that it belongs to the information theory (cs.IT) category. The paper also discusses the use of random matrices and their properties, which are commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques to solve the matrix completion problem, which is a common topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the construction of a class of matrices that can be recovered with a small probability of error, which is related to statistical inference (cs.SI).
